cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.CY 

This paper belongs to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category as it deals with Internet-wide scans and ICMP responses to study the Internet's control plane. It also involves aspects of Computer and Network Security (cs.CR) as it uncovers control plane problems such as outdated and misconfigured routers and persistent routing loops. Additionally, it touches upon aspects of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as it studies the domain name space. Information Theory (cs.IT) and Cybersecurity (cs.CY) are also possible categories as the paper deals with information transmission and security issues.
